entry.def: If you describe something such as a work of art or a piece of work as unfinished, you mean that it is not complete, for example because it was abandoned or there was no time to complete it.

example.tran: 简·奥斯汀未完成的小说

example.ex: The cathedral was eventually completed in 1490, though the Gothic facade remains unfinished...
example.tran: 那座大教堂最终于1490年建成，但其哥特式风格的正面一直未能完工。

means.word_mean: 1. not brought to the desired final state
2. not brought to an end or conclusion;
3. lacking a surface finish such as paint;
